Description:
   Fireshield surrounds the caster in a blazing shield of flame. It is the
   most aggressive of the magic shields, dealing significant reactive fire
   damage to any attacker while also absorbing a portion of incoming damage.

   Shield properties:
     - Type: FLAME_SHIELD (cannot stack with other non-coexisting shields)
     - Reactive Damage: 30% of incoming damage dealt back as fire damage
     - Absorption: 10% + (pseudo_level / 10)% of incoming damage absorbed
     - Hit Points: 5,000 + (pseudo_level * 10) -- shield breaks when depleted
     - Duration: pseudo_level / 10 rounds (halved on login)

   The reactive fire damage bypasses cloak reflection and absorption effects.
   Only one non-coexisting shield may be active at a time (fireshield,
   shockshield, etc). Iceshield and arcaneshield may coexist with it.
